{"key":"post-13258575","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13258575</id>\n<content>Sunlight this time of year when the sun is lower on the horizon is just fine.&amp;nbsp; If it's being diffused by a window and by a fruiting chamber, it's not really direct sunlight.&amp;nbsp; As long as the tub isn't heating up excessively inside, it's fine.&amp;nbsp; The sunlight won't damage the mycelium.&amp;nbsp; It's a good pinning trigger, but obviously not the biggest one.&amp;nbsp; You still need lots of fresh air, and misting to replace the lost&amp;nbsp; moisture.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;My biggest and best performing substrates right now are the ones outdoors in direct sun most of the day.&amp;nbsp; Obviously, someone in a hot climate won't put substrates outdoors in direct sun, but if your outdoor temperatures are cool, then it's great.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13259143</next>\n<prev>13258561</prev>\n<first>13258051</first>\n<last>22879322</last>\n<when>1285693350</when>\n<utime>09/28/10 08:02 PM</utime>\n</post>"}